      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get what ur saying about peer review being the standard, but that's the problem... the peers are the ones in on it. if the discovery itself was world-altering, the whole system would be part of the cover up. i'm not looking for a textbook answer, i'm looking for what's *between* the lines. if we look at the photographic data or the telemetry logs from those specific years, can you help me analyze them for technical anomalies or weird redactions that they'd use to mask something out?",
